If we were to follow your viewpoints on the world, racial minorities would still not be afforded the civil rights that they have today (because the Constitution, as ruled in Dred Scott v. Sandford, was written for "white people" as opposed to all people).Changing a definition in order to insure protection of civil rights is more just than holding onto a definition that wrongfully denies civil rights.